HEADWORD: Forehook
<hw>Fore"hook`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A piece of timber placed across the stem, to unite the bows and
strengthen the fore part of the ship; a breast hook.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

